@ydai1124 , There are a lot of differences between the existing gobblin-retention for hive datasets and this one. 
1) In existing one, hive dataset refers to a hive table, here it is at partition level.
2) In existing one, there is no versioning scheme which can suit the requirement. Example versions of a hive dataset(table) are partitions (hence time based version policy) in the existing one while in this one, versions of a hive dataset(partition) are backup/staging data of the same partition.

